#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:94
msgid ""
"On macOS, Emacs cannot inherit environment variables (such as ~$PATH~) from "
"the shell, so "
"[[https://github.com/purcell/exec-path-from-shell][exec-path-from-shell]] is "
"needed as a workaround.  "
"[[https://github.com/d12frosted/homebrew-emacs-plus/blob/3e61ee44f4cfc43dce292047aff5e9277e7d1bd4/Library/EmacsBase.rb#L33-L49][emacs-plus]] "
"injects PATH into Emacs's Info.plist, so applying that patch might eliminate "
"the need for this package."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:98
msgid ""
"=exec-path-from-shell-initialize= replaces =exec-path= with the login "
"shell's ~PATH~.  Merging =my/nix-exec-path= back after initialization "
"preserves wrapper-provided paths."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:102
msgid ""
"When launched from an application launcher (Dock, Spotlight), Emacs inherits "
"only the minimal launchd environment, which lacks Nix-related "
"variables. Without these, =direnv export= may produce incomplete "
"results. ([[https://github.com/purcell/envrc/issues/92][envrc#92]])"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:107
msgid ""
"Separately, fish sources =conf.d/*.fish= even for non-interactive "
"invocations (=fish -c \"...\"=). nix-darwin places environment setup scripts "
"there that re-initialize PATH from system profiles when guard variables "
"(=__fish_nixos_env_preinit_sourced=, =__NIX_DARWIN_SET_ENVIRONMENT_DONE=, "
"=__HM_SESS_VARS_SOURCED=) are absent. Without propagating these guards, "
"subprocesses spawned by =compile= or =shell-command= lose the buffer-local "
"PATH that envrc constructed—even though envrc itself applied the correct "
"environment."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:117
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(use-package exec-path-from-shell\n"
"  :ensure t\n"
"  :config\n"
"  (when (memq window-system '(mac ns x))\n"
"    (dolist (var '(\"SSH_AUTH_SOCK\" \"SSH_AGENT_PID\" \"GPG_AGENT_INFO\"\n"
"                   \"LANG\" \"LC_CTYPE\" \"NIX_SSL_CERT_FILE\" "
"\"NIX_PATH\"\n"
"                   \"__fish_nixos_env_preinit_sourced\"\n"
"                   \"__NIX_DARWIN_SET_ENVIRONMENT_DONE\"\n"
"                   \"__HM_SESS_VARS_SOURCED\"))\n"
"      (add-to-list 'exec-path-from-shell-variables var))\n"
"    (exec-path-from-shell-initialize)\n"
"    (setq exec-path (delete-dups (append exec-path my/nix-exec-path)))))"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading **
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:131
#, no-wrap
msgid "envrc"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:133
msgid ""
"[[https://github.com/purcell/envrc][envrc.el]] provides buffer-local "
"environment variables based on direnv. This enables Emacs to recognize "
"project-specific development environments managed by direnv."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:137
msgid ""
"Unlike direnv.el which sets environment variables globally, envrc.el keeps "
"them buffer-local. This is essential when working on multiple projects "
"simultaneously, each with its own .envrc."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:141
msgid ""
"The mode must be enabled early (via after-init hook) so that other packages "
"can inherit the correct environment."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:144
msgid ""
"When envrc updates a buffer's environment, it replaces =exec-path= with "
"values from =direnv export=, losing the Nix wrapper paths.  "
"([[https://github.com/purcell/envrc/issues/9][envrc#9]])  Merging "
"=my/nix-exec-path= back after each update preserves access to "
"wrapper-provided executables (e.g. yaml-language-server)  inside "
"direnv-managed buffers."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:153
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(use-package envrc\n"
"  :ensure t\n"
"  :hook (after-init . envrc-global-mode)\n"
"  :config\n"
"  (advice-add 'envrc--update :after\n"
"    (defun my/envrc-preserve-nix-path (&rest _)\n"
"      (when (local-variable-p 'exec-path)\n"
"        (setq-local exec-path\n"
"                    (delete-dups (append exec-path my/nix-exec-path)))))))"
msgstr ""

