#. type: heading ***
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:301
#, no-wrap
msgid "forge"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:303
msgid ""
"[[https://github.com/magit/forge][Forge]] extends Magit to work with GitHub, "
"GitLab, and other forges directly from Emacs—browsing issues, reviewing pull "
"requests, and managing notifications without leaving the editor."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:307
msgid ""
"Forge authenticates via =ghub=, which reads credentials from "
"=auth-sources=.  The =authinfo.age= file should contain a GitHub API token "
"entry:"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in example
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:311
#, no-wrap
msgid "machine api.github.com login <username>^forge password <token>"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:314
msgid ""
"The token must be a [[https://github.com/settings/tokens/new][classic "
"personal access token]], not a fine-grained one, because the "
"=/notifications= REST endpoints only accept classic tokens. A 6-month "
"expiration is set so the token must be regenerated periodically."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:318
msgid "Required scopes:"
msgstr ""

#. type: plain list -
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:321
#, no-wrap
msgid "=repo= — issues and pull requests"
msgstr ""

#. type: plain list -
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:322
#, no-wrap
msgid "=notifications= — =forge-list-notifications= and notification marking"
msgstr ""

#. type: plain list -
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:323
#, no-wrap
msgid "=user= — resolve the authenticated user's profile"
msgstr ""

#. type: plain list -
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:324
#, no-wrap
msgid "=read:org= — enumerate organization repositories and teams"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:326
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(use-package forge\n"
"  :ensure t\n"
"  :after magit)"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:331
#, no-wrap
msgid "consult-gh"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:333
msgid ""
"[[https://github.com/armindarvish/consult-gh][consult-gh]] drives the =gh= "
"CLI through a consult interface, so searching repositories, issues, pull "
"requests, and code across GitHub happens from the minibuffer with live "
"preview."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:337
msgid ""
"Forge already covers issues and pull requests for repositories tracked "
"locally in magit. consult-gh extends that reach to arbitrary repositories: "
"scanning an upstream's recent issues, opening another project's README, or "
"finding a snippet by code search—without first cloning or visiting the repo "
"in magit."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:343
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(use-package consult-gh\n"
"  :ensure t\n"
"  :after consult\n"
"  :config\n"
"  (consult-gh-enable-default-keybindings))"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:350
msgid ""
"=consult-gh-embark-mode= adds embark actions on results (clone, browse, copy "
"URL, ...)."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:354
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(use-package consult-gh-embark\n"
"  :ensure t\n"
"  :after (consult-gh embark)\n"
"  :config\n"
"  (consult-gh-embark-mode +1))"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:361
msgid ""
"=consult-gh-forge-mode= routes issue and PR viewing through forge buffers, "
"keeping the editing surface consistent with the existing magit/forge "
"workflow."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:365
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(use-package consult-gh-forge\n"
"  :ensure t\n"
"  :after (consult-gh forge)\n"
"  :config\n"
"  (consult-gh-forge-mode +1))"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading *
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:372
#, no-wrap
msgid "LSP"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:374
msgid ""
"[[https://emacs-lsp.github.io/lsp-mode/][lsp-mode]] is a Language Server "
"Protocol client for Emacs.  It provides IDE-like features (completion, "
"diagnostics, navigation)  by communicating with external language servers."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:378
msgid ""
"Eglot is built into Emacs 29+ as a lighter alternative, but it assumes one "
"server per major mode, making it cumbersome to run multiple servers "
"simultaneously on the same buffer (e.g. a language server alongside a linter "
"or formatter).  lsp-mode handles multiple concurrent servers natively and "
"provides more granular control over LSP behavior."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:385
msgid ""
"Using =lsp-deferred= instead of =lsp= to delay server startup until the "
"buffer is visible, avoiding unnecessary processes for buffers opened in the "
"background."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:389
msgid ""
"Disabling =lsp-headerline-breadcrumb-mode= to avoid conflict with the "
"existing =breadcrumb= package in the header line."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:393
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(use-package lsp-mode\n"
"  :ensure t\n"
"  :commands (lsp lsp-deferred)\n"
"  :init\n"
"  (setq lsp-keymap-prefix \"C-c l\")\n"
"  :config\n"
"  (setq lsp-headerline-breadcrumb-enable nil))"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading *
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:402
#, no-wrap
msgid "language support"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading **
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:404
#, no-wrap
msgid "tree-sitter"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:406
msgid "Use maximum font-lock level for tree-sitter modes."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:409
#, no-wrap
msgid "(setq treesit-font-lock-level 4)"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading **
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:412
#, no-wrap
msgid "treesit-fold"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:414
msgid ""
"[[https://github.com/emacs-tree-sitter/treesit-fold][treesit-fold]] provides "
"code folding driven by the tree-sitter syntax tree, so foldable regions "
"follow real syntactic nodes (functions, blocks, comments) rather than "
"indentation heuristics."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:419
msgid ""
"=global-treesit-fold-mode= activates it automatically in every supported "
"tree-sitter mode."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:422
msgid ""
"TAB is rebound to a wrapper that mimics =org-cycle=: when point sits on a "
"foldable node, the fold is toggled; otherwise the original "
"=indent-for-tab-command= runs, so ordinary indentation in code keeps "
"working."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:427
msgid ""
"Language-specific fold rules (e.g. Nix =let ... in= blocks) live with their "
"respective language sections rather than here, so the catalogue of foldable "
"nodes per language stays next to the rest of that mode's setup."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:432
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(use-package treesit-fold\n"
"  :ensure t\n"
"  :hook (after-init . global-treesit-fold-mode)\n"
"  :preface\n"
"  (defun my/treesit-fold-toggle-or-indent ()\n"
"    \"Toggle the fold at point when on a foldable node; otherwise "
"indent.\"\n"
"    (interactive)\n"
"    (if (treesit-fold--foldable-node-at-pos)\n"
"        (treesit-fold-toggle)\n"
"      (indent-for-tab-command)))\n"
"  :bind (:map treesit-fold-mode-map\n"
"              (\"TAB\" . my/treesit-fold-toggle-or-indent)))"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading **
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:446
#, no-wrap
msgid "Beancount"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:448
msgid ""
"[[https://github.com/beancount/beancount-mode][beancount-mode]] is the major "
"mode bundled with [[https://beancount.github.io/][Beancount]].  LSP "
"integration uses "
"[[https://github.com/polarmutex/beancount-language-server][beancount-language-server]] "
"via lsp-mode's bundled =lsp-beancount= client."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:452
msgid ""
"Upstream only auto-registers =.beancount=, so =.bean= is added explicitly "
"here for the common short extension."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:456
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(use-package beancount\n"
"  :ensure t\n"
"  :mode (\"\\\\.bean\\\\(count\\\\)?\\\\'\" . beancount-mode)\n"
"  :hook (beancount-mode . lsp-deferred))"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading **
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:462
#, no-wrap
msgid "CSV"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:464
msgid ""
"[[https://elpa.gnu.org/packages/csv-mode.html][csv-mode]] provides a major "
"mode for editing csv and tsv files."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:467
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(use-package csv-mode\n"
"  :ensure t)"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading **
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:471
#, no-wrap
msgid "Markdown"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:473
msgid "https://github.com/jrblevin/markdown-mode"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in quote
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:476
msgid "markdown-mode is a major mode for editing Markdown-formatted text."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:479
msgid ""
"First, enable =markdown-fontify-code-blocks-natively= so fenced code blocks "
"are highlighted by each language's major mode. A =```nix= block then reads "
"like a real Nix buffer rather than a flat monochrome region."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:483
msgid ""
"Also enable =markdown-marginalize-headers= to push leading =#= characters "
"into the left margin. Header text then starts at the same column across all "
"depths, keeping the outline aligned with body paragraphs."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:488
msgid ""
"Finally, set =markdown-indent-on-enter= to ='indent-and-new-item= so =RET= "
"inside a list inserts the next bullet or number at the correct indent level."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:493
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(use-package markdown-mode\n"
"  :ensure t\n"
"  :mode (\"README\\\\.md\\\\'\" . gfm-mode)\n"
"  :init (setq markdown-command \"multimarkdown\")\n"
"  :bind (:map markdown-mode-map\n"
"              (\"C-c C-e\" . markdown-do))\n"
"  :config\n"
"  (setq markdown-header-scaling t)\n"
"  (setq markdown-fontify-code-blocks-natively t)\n"
"  (setq markdown-marginalize-headers t)\n"
"  (setq markdown-indent-on-enter 'indent-and-new-item))"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:508
msgid "https://github.com/nix-community/nix-ts-mode"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:510
msgid "Tree-sitter based major mode for Nix expressions."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:512
msgid ""
"[[https://github.com/nix-community/nixd][nixd]] (configured via lsp-mode) "
"provides IDE features for Nix expressions by interoperating with the C++ Nix "
"evaluator.  Unlike nil which relies on static analysis, nixd performs actual "
"Nix evaluation, enabling accurate completion for attribute paths "
"(e.g. =pkgs.=), NixOS options, and flake inputs."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:519
msgid ""
"The bundled =treesit-fold-parsers-nix= only knows about attrsets, "
"interpolations, lists, and comments. Two extra rules are registered here so "
"=let ... in= blocks and indented (=''...''=) multi-line strings fold as "
"well."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:525
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(use-package nix-ts-mode\n"
"  :ensure t\n"
"  :mode \"\\\\.nix\\\\'\"\n"
"  :hook (nix-ts-mode . lsp-deferred)\n"
"  :init\n"
"  ;; org-src-lang-modes is defined in org-src, which may not be loaded yet "
"at init time\n"
"  (with-eval-after-load 'org-src\n"
"    (add-to-list 'org-src-lang-modes '(\"nix\" . nix-ts)))\n"
"  :config\n"
"  (setq lsp-nix-nixd-formatting-command [\"nixfmt\"])\n"
"  (with-eval-after-load 'treesit-fold\n"
"    (setf (alist-get 'nix-ts-mode treesit-fold-range-alist)\n"
"          (append (alist-get 'nix-ts-mode treesit-fold-range-alist)\n"
"                  `((let_expression\n"
"                     . ,(lambda (node offset)\n"
"                          (treesit-fold-range-markers node offset \"let\" "
"\"in\")))\n"
"                    (indented_string_expression\n"
"                     . ,(lambda (node offset)\n"
"                          (treesit-fold-range-markers node offset \"''\" "
"\"''\"))))))))"
msgstr ""

