#. type: heading **
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:717
#, no-wrap
msgid "org-gcal"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:719
msgid ""
"[[https://github.com/kidd/org-gcal.el][org-gcal]] provides bidirectional "
"sync between Google Calendar and Org files via the native Google Calendar "
"API."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:723
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(use-package org-gcal\n"
"  :ensure t\n"
"  :defer t)"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:728
msgid "Prerequisites for this configuration to function:"
msgstr ""

#. type: plain list 1.
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:733
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"On the personal Cloud Project, the Google Calendar API is enabled\n"
"and =https://www.googleapis.com/auth/calendar= is added\n"
"to the OAuth consent screen scopes."
msgstr ""

#. type: plain list 2.
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:738
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"=~/.authinfo.age= contains entries:\n"
"#+begin_example\n"
"machine org-gcal login client-id password <client-id>\n"
"machine org-gcal login client-secret password <client-secret>\n"
"#+end_example"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:739
msgid ""
"org-gcal registers an =oauth2-auto= provider entry at package load time only "
"when both =org-gcal-client-id= and =org-gcal-client-secret= are already set; "
"otherwise it skips registration and warns.  Since these variables are "
"populated after the package loads, =org-gcal-reload-client-id-secret= must "
"be called explicitly to perform the registration with the populated values."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:747
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(with-eval-after-load 'org-gcal\n"
"  (setq org-gcal-client-id\n"
"        (auth-source-pick-first-password :host \"org-gcal\" :user "
"\"client-id\"))\n"
"  (setq org-gcal-client-secret\n"
"        (auth-source-pick-first-password :host \"org-gcal\" :user "
"\"client-secret\"))\n"
"  (org-gcal-reload-client-id-secret))"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:755
msgid ""
"org-gcal supports only one global OAuth client.  To sync calendars from "
"multiple accounts, share the secondary calendars to the authorized account "
"via Google Calendar's sharing UI with \"Make changes to events\" permission."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:761
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(with-eval-after-load 'org-gcal\n"
"  (setq org-gcal-fetch-file-alist\n"
"        `((\"tomoya.otabi@gmail.com\" . ,(concat org-root "
"\"gcal-personal.org\"))\n"
"          (\"tomoya.otabi@attm.co.jp\" . ,(concat org-root "
"\"gcal-work.org\")))))"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:767
msgid ""
"The empty-file pre-creation works around "
"[[https://github.com/telotortium/emacs-oauth2-auto/issues/6][emacs-oauth2-auto "
"issue #6]]: when =~/.config/emacs/= contains symlinks (here from "
"home-manager managing other emacs config files), oauth2-auto's first write "
"to the plstore fails an internal file/buffer identity check.  Pre-creating "
"the file before the first sync lets that check succeed."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:775
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(with-eval-after-load 'oauth2-auto\n"
"  (unless (file-exists-p oauth2-auto-plstore)\n"
"    (write-region \"\" nil oauth2-auto-plstore)))"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:780
msgid ""
"org-gcal stores one plstore entry per calendar ID and each one is read on "
"every sync to retrieve the access token, so without passphrase caching the "
"user is prompted by pinentry multiple times per sync.  "
"=plstore-cache-passphrase-for-symmetric-encryption= caches the passphrase "
"within the Emacs session to reduce this to a single prompt after Emacs "
"restart."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:789
#, no-wrap
msgid "(setq plstore-cache-passphrase-for-symmetric-encryption t)"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:794
msgid ""
"[[https://git.natsukium.com/natsukium/org-clickup][org-clickup]] is a "
"personal package that bidirectionally syncs ClickUp tasks with org-mode TODO "
"entries. Work tasks live in ClickUp, but the authoritative planning surface "
"is org-mode (agenda, capture, refile)  so daily triage stays in Emacs "
"instead of switching to a browser tab."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:799
msgid "The API token must live in =~/.authinfo.age= as:"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in example
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:802
#, no-wrap
msgid "machine api.clickup.com login <workspace-id> password <token>"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:806
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(use-package org-clickup\n"
"  :ensure t\n"
"  :defer t)"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading **
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:811
#, no-wrap
msgid "org-roam"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:813
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(use-package org-roam\n"
"  :ensure t\n"
"  :custom\n"
"  (org-roam-directory \"~/dropbox/org-roam\")\n"
"  (org-roam-db-location \"~/.local/share/org-roam.db\")\n"
"  :bind\n"
"  ((\"C-c n l\" . org-roam-buffer-toggle)\n"
"   (\"C-c n f\" . org-roam-node-find)\n"
"   (\"C-c n g\" . org-roam-graph)\n"
"   (\"C-c n i\" . org-roam-node-insert)\n"
"   (\"C-c n c\" . org-roam-capture)\n"
"   (\"C-c n j\" . org-roam-dailies-capture-today))\n"
"  :config\n"
"  (setq org-roam-capture-templates\n"
"        '((\"p\" \"permanent\" plain \"%?\"\n"
"           :target (file+head \"permanent/${slug}.org\" \"#+title: "
"${title}\\n\")\n"
"           :unnarrowed t)\n"
"          (\"l\" \"literature\" plain \"%?\"\n"
"           :target (file+head \"literature/${title}.org\" \"#+title: "
"${title}\\n\")\n"
"           :unnarrowed t)))\n"
"  (setq org-roam-node-display-template\n"
"        (concat \"${title:*} \"\n"
"                (propertize \"${tags:10}\" 'face 'org-tag)))\n"
"  (org-roam-db-autosync-mode)\n"
"  (require 'org-roam-protocol)\n"
"  )"
msgstr ""

