#. type: heading *
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:914
#, no-wrap
msgid "mail"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:916
msgid ""
"[[https://notmuchmail.org/][notmuch]] is a tag-based email indexer and "
"searcher.  [[https://notmuchmail.org/notmuch-emacs/][notmuch.el]] provides "
"an Emacs interface for reading and organizing email.  It reads mail from a "
"local maildir synced by mbsync."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:920
msgid ""
"notmuch was chosen over mu4e because the notmuch indexer is already "
"configured for all email accounts.  Adding notmuch.el only requires the "
"Emacs frontend, avoiding a second indexer for the same maildir."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:925
msgid ""
"notmuch has no built-in delete operation; it manages metadata (tags)  rather "
"than maildir folder placement.  Pressing =d= tags the message with "
"=+deleted= and removes =inbox=.  The actual deletion happens on the next "
"=notmuch new=: a post-new hook moves tagged files to Gmail's Trash maildir "
"folder after indexing, so the move is synced to the server on the next "
"mbsync run.  =D= reverses the operation, restoring =inbox= and removing "
"=deleted=.  This only works before the next =notmuch new= moves the file; "
"once mbsync has synced the move, the message is in Gmail's Trash."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:935
msgid ""
"=shr-use-colors= is disabled so sender HTML colors don't clash with the dark "
"theme. Inline CID images ship with the mail and are enabled, but "
"=shr-blocked-images= is set to =.= (matches every URL) to block remote "
"images, which marketing platforms use as tracking pixels — Gmail's web UI "
"proxies them, but notmuch fetches directly. =I= refreshes the current "
"message with blocking disabled when a sender is trusted."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:942
msgid ""
"=notmuch-show-part-button-default-action= defaults to saving an attachment "
"to disk; I switch it to =notmuch-show-view-part= so the part opens with its "
"mailcap viewer instead, letting me press the button on a PDF to open it "
"directly."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:948
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(use-package notmuch\n"
"  :ensure nil\n"
"  :bind (\"C-c M\" . notmuch)\n"
"  :custom\n"
"  (notmuch-fcc-dirs nil)\n"
"  (notmuch-search-oldest-first nil)\n"
"  (notmuch-show-part-button-default-action 'notmuch-show-view-part)\n"
"  (notmuch-saved-searches\n"
"   '((:name \"inbox\"    :query \"tag:inbox\"                                      "
":key \"i\")\n"
"     (:name \"unread\"   :query \"tag:unread\"                                     "
":key \"u\")\n"
"     (:name \"action\"   :query \"tag:github::action-required\"                    "
":key \"a\")\n"
"     (:name \"attmcojp\" :query \"tag:github::attmcojp\"                           "
":key \"w\")\n"
"     (:name \"github\"   :query \"tag:github and not "
"tag:github::action-required\" :key \"g\")\n"
"     (:name \"all\"      :query \"*\"                                              "
":key \"A\")))\n"
"  (shr-use-colors nil)\n"
"  (mm-inline-text-html-with-images t)\n"
"  (shr-blocked-images \".\")\n"
"  :config\n"
"  (keymap-set notmuch-search-mode-map \"d\"\n"
"    (lambda ()\n"
"      (interactive)\n"
"      (notmuch-search-tag '(\"+deleted\" \"-inbox\"))\n"
"      (notmuch-search-next-thread)))\n"
"  (keymap-set notmuch-show-mode-map \"d\"\n"
"    (lambda ()\n"
"      (interactive)\n"
"      (notmuch-show-tag '(\"+deleted\" \"-inbox\"))))\n"
"  (keymap-set notmuch-search-mode-map \"D\"\n"
"    (lambda ()\n"
"      (interactive)\n"
"      (notmuch-search-tag '(\"-deleted\" \"+inbox\"))\n"
"      (notmuch-search-next-thread)))\n"
"  (keymap-set notmuch-show-mode-map \"D\"\n"
"    (lambda ()\n"
"      (interactive)\n"
"      (notmuch-show-tag '(\"-deleted\" \"+inbox\"))))\n"
"  (keymap-set notmuch-show-mode-map \"I\"\n"
"    (lambda ()\n"
"      (interactive)\n"
"      (let ((shr-blocked-images nil))\n"
"        (notmuch-show-refresh-view t)))))"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:991
msgid ""
"[[https://orgmode.org/manual/Protocols.html][ol-notmuch]] integrates notmuch "
"with Org mode's link system.  Calling =org-store-link= (=C-c l=) in a "
"notmuch buffer stores a link to the current message or thread, which can "
"then be inserted into org-capture templates via =%a=."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/features/emacs/init.org:997
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(use-package ol-notmuch\n"
"  :ensure t\n"
"  :after (notmuch org))"
msgstr ""

