msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:769
#, no-wrap
msgid "Nix Remote Build"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:771
msgid ""
"Abbreviations for specifying Nix build target systems, primarily used when "
"working on nixpkgs. Each abbreviation expands to =--system <triple>= and "
"conditionally appends =-j0= when the target system differs from the current "
"host. =-j0= sets the local job limit to zero, forcing all builds to be "
"delegated to remote builders (see [[*Distributed Builds][Distributed "
"Builds]]). This prevents Nix from accidentally attempting to build on the "
"host, which would fail with an architecture mismatch."
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:778
#, no-wrap
msgid "fish-abbr-nix"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:780
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\"--sxl\" = {\n"
"  position = \"anywhere\";\n"
"  expansion =\n"
"    \"--system x86_64-linux\"\n"
"    + pkgs.lib.optionalString (\n"
"      pkgs.stdenv.hostPlatform.isDarwin || "
"pkgs.stdenv.hostPlatform.isAarch64\n"
"    ) \" -j0\";\n"
"};\n"
"\"--sal\" = {\n"
"  position = \"anywhere\";\n"
"  expansion =\n"
"    \"--system aarch64-linux\"\n"
"    + pkgs.lib.optionalString (\n"
"      pkgs.stdenv.hostPlatform.isDarwin || "
"pkgs.stdenv.hostPlatform.isx86_64\n"
"    ) \" -j0\";\n"
"};\n"
"\"--sxd\" = {\n"
"  position = \"anywhere\";\n"
"  expansion =\n"
"    \"--system x86_64-darwin\" + pkgs.lib.optionalString "
"pkgs.stdenv.hostPlatform.isLinux \" -j0\";\n"
"};\n"
"\"--sad\" = {\n"
"  position = \"anywhere\";\n"
"  expansion =\n"
"    \"--system aarch64-darwin\" + pkgs.lib.optionalString "
"pkgs.stdenv.hostPlatform.isLinux \" -j0\";\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:809
#, no-wrap
msgid "Functions"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:811
msgid ""
"Helper functions used by the abbreviation system. These are separated from "
"the abbreviation definitions because fish requires functions to be defined "
"before they can be referenced by =--function= abbreviations."
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:815
#, no-wrap
msgid "fish-functions"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:817
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"functions = {\n"
"  _abbr_last_history_item = \"echo $history[1]\";\n"
"  _abbr_extract_tar_gz = \"echo tar avfx $argv\";\n"
"  _abbr_multicd = \"echo cd (string repeat -n (math (string length -- "
"$argv[1]) - 1) ../)\";\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:824
#, no-wrap
msgid "any-nix-shell"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:826
msgid ""
"[[https://github.com/haslersn/any-nix-shell][any-nix-shell]] keeps fish as "
"the interactive shell inside =nix shell= and =nix develop= environments; "
"without it, entering a Nix shell drops into bash and loses fish's "
"interactive features."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:830
msgid ""
"=any-nix-shell fish= only emits two function definitions (=nix= and "
"=nix-shell=), but generating them shells out to =/bin/sh= plus three =which= "
"lookups — ~24ms on every interactive startup if sourced eagerly. Running it "
"once at build time and splitting the output into fish's autoload directory "
"moves that cost off the hot path (fish parses each function on first call), "
"and uses any-nix-shell's real wrappers rather than a hardcoded copy, so its "
"=nix run= version gate and =--pure= handling stay in sync with the upstream "
"package."
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:838
#, no-wrap
msgid "fish-any-nix-shell"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:843
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"anyNixShellFunction =\n"
"  name:\n"
"  pkgs.runCommand \"any-nix-shell-${name}.fish\" { nativeBuildInputs = [ "
"pkgs.any-nix-shell ]; } ''\n"
"    any-nix-shell fish | awk -v want=${name} '\n"
"      $1 == \"function\" { current = $2; depth = 0 }\n"
"      current == want {\n"
"        print\n"
"        if ($1 ~ /^(function|begin|if|for|while|switch)$/) depth++\n"
"        else if ($1 == \"end\" && --depth == 0) current = \"\"\n"
"      }\n"
"    ' > $out\n"
"  '';"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:857
#, no-wrap
msgid "Plugins"
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:859
#, no-wrap
msgid "fish-plugins"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:861
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"plugins = [\n"
"  {\n"
"    name = \"done\";\n"
"    src = pkgs.fishPlugins.done.src;\n"
"  }\n"
"  {\n"
"    name = \"fzf-fish\";\n"
"    src = pkgs.fishPlugins.fzf-fish.src;\n"
"  }\n"
"];"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:873
msgid ""
"The [[https://github.com/franciscolourenco/done][done]] plugin provides "
"desktop notifications for long-running commands.  The threshold is set to 15 "
"seconds — commands shorter than this are typically interactive and do not "
"benefit from notifications, while longer commands (builds, test suites, "
"large file operations) are often run in the background where a notification "
"is valuable."
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:879
#, no-wrap
msgid "fish-done-config"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:882
#, no-wrap
msgid "set -U __done_min_cmd_duration 15000"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:885
msgid ""
"[[https://github.com/PatrickF1/fzf.fish][fzf-fish]] integrates fzf with "
"fish's tab completion, history search, and file/directory navigation. It "
"replaces fish's built-in history search (=Ctrl+R=) with fzf's fuzzy finder, "
"which handles large histories more effectively."
msgstr ""

#. type: heading **
#: modules/configuration.org:889
#, no-wrap
msgid "Bash"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:891
msgid ""
"Bash is configured as a minimal fallback shell rather than a full "
"interactive environment. The primary use case is ensuring a usable shell "
"exists when fish is unavailable, and providing a POSIX-compatible shell for "
"scripts and tools that assume bash. It also serves as a testing environment "
"when fish exhibits unexpected behaviour — having a clean bash available "
"helps isolate whether an issue is fish-specific."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:898
msgid ""
"Registered as a home-manager feature behind =my.programs.bash.enable=, "
"matching the toggle every other shell in this section already has, rather "
"than applying unconditionally to every home that imports the profile it used "
"to live in."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:908
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{ ... }:\n"
"{\n"
"  flake.modules.homeManager.bash =\n"
"    {\n"
"      pkgs,\n"
"      lib,\n"
"      config,\n"
"      ...\n"
"    }:\n"
"    let\n"
"      cfg = config.my.programs.bash;\n"
"    in\n"
"    {\n"
"      options.my.programs.bash.enable = lib.mkEnableOption \"bash\";"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:923
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"config = lib.mkIf cfg.enable {\n"
"  home.packages = with pkgs; [ bashInteractive ];\n"
"  programs.bash = {\n"
"    enable = true;"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:928
#, no-wrap
msgid "<<bash-history>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:930
#, no-wrap
msgid "<<bash-completion>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:932
#, no-wrap
msgid "<<bash-aliases>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:934
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"          <<bash-init>>\n"
"        };\n"
"      };\n"
"    };\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:941
#, no-wrap
msgid "History"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:943
msgid ""
"History is stored under =XDG_CONFIG_HOME= to keep =$HOME= clean, consistent "
"with the repository's preference for XDG base directories (see [[*User-Level "
"Settings][User-Level Settings]])."
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:946
#, no-wrap
msgid "bash-history"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:948
#, no-wrap
msgid "historyFile = \"$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/bash/history\";"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:951
#, no-wrap
msgid "Completion"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:953
msgid ""
"Bash completion is disabled because bash is not used as the primary "
"interactive shell. Loading completion scripts adds startup time (~100ms+) "
"with no benefit when the shell is only used as a fallback or for running "
"scripts."
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:957
#, no-wrap
msgid "bash-completion"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:959
#, no-wrap
msgid "enableCompletion = false;"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:962
#, no-wrap
msgid "Aliases"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:964
msgid ""
"Basic aliases that provide a minimal quality-of-life improvement if bash is "
"used interactively. These are intentionally simple — fish handles the rich "
"interactive experience."
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:968
#, no-wrap
msgid "bash-aliases"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:970
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"shellAliases = {\n"
"  l = \"ls -CF\";\n"
"  grep = \"grep --color=auto\";\n"
"  fgrep = \"fgrep --color=auto\";\n"
"  egrep = \"egrep --color=auto\";\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:978
#, no-wrap
msgid "Init"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:980
msgid ""
"This configuration is a remnant from before fish was set as the default "
"login shell.  Previously, bash was the login shell and =.bashrc= launched "
"fish, so these settings were needed in every interactive session. They are "
"retained because bash is still used as a fallback."
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:985
#, no-wrap
msgid "bash-init"
msgstr ""

#. type: plain list +
#: modules/configuration.org:992
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"lib.optionalString (!config.programs.kitty.enable) ''\n"
"<<bash-tmux-autostart>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:987
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"initExtra = ''\n"
"  <<bash-terminal-settings>>\n"
"''\n"
"'';"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:995
#, no-wrap
msgid "Terminal Settings"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:997
msgid ""
"=stty stop undef= disables =Ctrl+S= from sending =XOFF=, freeing it for use "
"as a keybinding in fish and other TUI applications. Without it, =Ctrl+S= "
"freezes the terminal until =Ctrl+Q= is pressed."
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1001
#, no-wrap
msgid "bash-terminal-settings"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1003
#, no-wrap
msgid "stty stop undef  # Ctrl-s"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:1006
#, no-wrap
msgid "TMUX Auto-attach"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1008
msgid ""
"Automatically starts or attaches to a tmux session when bash is the "
"interactive shell, but only when kitty is not the terminal emulator. Kitty "
"has its own tab/window management (splits, layouts, tabs) that conflicts "
"with tmux's multiplexing — running tmux inside kitty creates redundant "
"nesting. When using a simpler terminal (e.g., =xterm=, =alacritty=, or a "
"Linux console), tmux provides the session persistence and window management "
"that would otherwise be missing."
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1015
#, no-wrap
msgid "bash-tmux-autostart"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1018
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"if type tmux > /dev/null 2>&1; then\n"
"  test -z $TMUX && tmux"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1023
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  while test -z $TMUX; do\n"
"    tmux attach || break\n"
"  done\n"
"fi"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading **
#: modules/configuration.org:1029
#, no-wrap
msgid "Readline"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1031
msgid ""
"readline provides line editing for bash and for most REPLs with a plain "
"prompt, such as the Python interpreter and =psql=. Configuring it here "
"rather than through bash keybindings covers all of them at once."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1035
msgid ""
"=Ctrl+W= deletes back to the previous =/= rather than the previous word "
"boundary, which suits the paths that make up most of what I type at a "
"prompt. The binding only holds with =bind-tty-special-chars= off: readline "
"otherwise copies the terminal's =werase= character into its keymap after "
"reading =inputrc=, which puts =Ctrl+W= back on =unix-word-rubout=."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1041
msgid "=completion-ignore-case= makes tab completion case-insensitive."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1049
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{ ... }:\n"
"{\n"
"  flake.modules.homeManager.readline =\n"
"    {\n"
"      lib,\n"
"      config,\n"
"      ...\n"
"    }:\n"
"    let\n"
"      cfg = config.my.programs.readline;\n"
"    in\n"
"    {\n"
"      options.my.programs.readline.enable = lib.mkEnableOption \"readline\";"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1063
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"config = lib.mkIf cfg.enable {\n"
"  programs.readline = {\n"
"    enable = true;"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1067
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"variables = {\n"
"  completion-ignore-case = true;\n"
"  bind-tty-special-chars = false;\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1072
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"          bindings = {\n"
"            \"\\\\C-w\" = \"unix-filename-rubout\";\n"
"          };\n"
"        };\n"
"      };\n"
"    };\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading **
#: modules/configuration.org:1081
#, no-wrap
msgid "Nushell"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1083
msgid ""
"Nushell is enabled for its ability to handle structured data natively, "
"similar to PowerShell. Where traditional shells pipe text between commands, "
"Nushell operates on serialised data formats (JSON, YAML, CSV, etc.) as "
"first-class tables and records, making simple data manipulation possible "
"without reaching for external tools like =jq=.  Like fish, it is non-POSIX, "
"but POSIX compatibility is not a requirement for an interactive shell."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1090
msgid ""
"No custom configuration is added yet — the defaults are sufficient for "
"exploratory use, and committing to Nushell-specific workflows would be "
"premature."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1093
msgid ""
"Registered behind =my.programs.nushell.enable=, like the other shells in "
"this section."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1101
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{ ... }:\n"
"{\n"
"  flake.modules.homeManager.nushell =\n"
"    {\n"
"      config,\n"
"      lib,\n"
"      pkgs,\n"
"      ...\n"
"    }:\n"
"    let\n"
"      cfg = config.my.programs.nushell;\n"
"      completerCfg = config.ext.programs.nushell.externalCompleter;\n"
"    in\n"
"    {\n"
"      options.my.programs.nushell.enable = lib.mkEnableOption \"nushell\";"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1117
#, no-wrap
msgid "<<nushell-external-completer-option>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1119
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"config = lib.mkMerge [\n"
"  (lib.mkIf cfg.enable {\n"
"    programs.nushell.enable = true;\n"
"  })"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1124
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"        <<nushell-external-completer-config>>\n"
"      ];\n"
"    };\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:1130
#, no-wrap
msgid "External Completer"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1132
msgid ""
"Nushell has no built-in tab-completion source for external (non-Nushell)  "
"commands. Piping candidates through fish's own completion engine reuses "
"every completion already defined for fish — package names, git subcommands, "
"CLI flags — instead of duplicating that logic in Nushell's completer syntax."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1137
msgid ""
"=externalCompleter= defaults to following whether Nushell itself is enabled, "
"so enabling the shell is enough to get external completions without a second "
"toggle; =enableFishCompleter= exists to opt out if fish is not the shell "
"doing the completing."
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1142
#, no-wrap
msgid "nushell-external-completer-option"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1144
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"options.ext.programs.nushell.externalCompleter = {\n"
"  enable = lib.mkOption {\n"
"    type = lib.types.bool;\n"
"    default = config.programs.nushell.enable;\n"
"  };\n"
"  enableFishCompleter = lib.mkOption {\n"
"    type = lib.types.bool;\n"
"    default = true;\n"
"  };\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1156
#, no-wrap
msgid "nushell-external-completer-config"
msgstr ""

#. type: cell column 0
#: modules/configuration.org:1162
#, no-wrap
msgid "$\"value(char tab)description(char newline)\" + $in"
msgstr ""

#. type: cell column 0
#: modules/configuration.org:1163
#, no-wrap
msgid "from tsv --flexible --no-infer"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1158
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(lib.mkIf completerCfg.enable {\n"
"  programs.nushell.extraConfig = lib.mkIf completerCfg.enableFishCompleter "
"''\n"
"    let fish_completer = {|spans|\n"
"        ${lib.getExe pkgs.fish} --command $'complete \"--do-complete=($spans "
"| str join \" \")\"'\n"
"    }"
msgstr ""

#. type: cell column 0
#: modules/configuration.org:1170
#, no-wrap
msgid "default {}"
msgstr ""

#. type: cell column 0
#: modules/configuration.org:1171
#, no-wrap
msgid "insert enable { true }"
msgstr ""

#. type: cell column 0
#: modules/configuration.org:1172
#, no-wrap
msgid "insert completer { $fish_completer }"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1166
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    $env.config = ($env.config? | default {})\n"
"    $env.config.completions = ($env.config.completions? | default {})\n"
"    $env.config.completions.external = (\n"
"        $env.config.completions.external?\n"
"    )\n"
"  '';\n"
"})"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading **
#: modules/configuration.org:1178
#, no-wrap
msgid "Starship"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1180
msgid ""
"[[https://starship.rs/][Starship]] is a cross-shell prompt written in Rust, "
"used across all shells configured here to provide a consistent prompt "
"experience. It has been used since its predecessor "
"[[https://github.com/matchai/spacefish][spacefish]], and its easy TOML-based "
"configuration is the main reason it has been kept."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1184
msgid ""
"Starship does not natively support asynchronous prompt rendering, so this "
"section also includes a custom async prompt module for fish."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1187
msgid ""
"Registered behind =my.programs.starship.enable=, with "
"=enableFishAsyncPrompt= as a second, independent toggle on the same module — "
"a host can run starship without the async prompt, but not the reverse."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1197
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{ ... }:\n"
"{\n"
"  flake.modules.homeManager.starship =\n"
"    {\n"
"      config,\n"
"      lib,\n"
"      ...\n"
"    }:\n"
"    let\n"
"      cfg = config.my.programs.starship;\n"
"    in\n"
"    {\n"
"      options.my.programs.starship = {\n"
"        enable = lib.mkEnableOption \"starship\";"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1212
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  enableFishAsyncPrompt = lib.mkOption {\n"
"    type = lib.types.bool;\n"
"    default = false;\n"
"  };\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1218
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"config = lib.mkMerge [\n"
"  (lib.mkIf cfg.enable {\n"
"    programs.starship = {\n"
"      enable = true;\n"
"      settings = builtins.fromTOML (builtins.readFile ./starship.toml);\n"
"    };\n"
"  })"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1226
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"        <<starship-async-prompt-config>>\n"
"      ];\n"
"    };\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:1237
#, no-wrap
msgid "Prompt Format"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1239
msgid ""
"The prompt format prepends a shell indicator before the default modules.  "
"This makes it immediately visible which shell is active, useful when "
"switching between fish and bash for testing or debugging."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1244
#, no-wrap
msgid "\"$schema\" = \"https://starship.rs/config-schema.json\""
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1246
#, no-wrap
msgid "format = \"$shell$all$line_break$character\""
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:1249
#, no-wrap
msgid "Shell Indicator"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1251
msgid ""
"Each shell has a distinct icon: =󰈺= (fish icon) for fish. Bash and nushell "
"use the default indicator."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1255
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[shell]\n"
"fish_indicator = \"󰈺\"\n"
"powershell_indicator = \"󰨊\"\n"
"disabled = false"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:1261
#, no-wrap
msgid "Remote Container Detection"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1263
msgid ""
"A custom module detects when running inside a VS Code Remote Container (Dev "
"Container) by checking the =REMOTE_CONTAINERS= environment variable, "
"displaying a whale emoji (🐋) as a visual reminder. This has not been used "
"for several years and may no longer be relevant."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1269
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[custom.remote-container]\n"
"when = \"\"\" test \"$REMOTE_CONTAINERS\" \"\"\"\n"
"symbol = \"🐋\"\n"
"format = \" in $symbol \""
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:1275
#, no-wrap
msgid "Disabled Modules"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1277
msgid ""
