#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:1638
#, no-wrap
msgid "Scalar"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1640
msgid ""
"[[https://git-scm.com/docs/scalar][Scalar]] optimizes git performance for "
"large repositories. Enabled specifically for the nixpkgs repository, which "
"contains over 600,000 commits and benefits significantly from Scalar's "
"background maintenance (prefetch, commit-graph, loose-objects) and "
"filesystem monitor integration."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1645
msgid ""
"=programs.git.scalar= is a custom option this module extends git with, "
"configuring git's built-in performance optimizations (multipack index, "
"preload index, untracked cache, fsmonitor) whenever a repository is "
"registered. It is a second toggle rather than folded into the base git "
"config unconditionally, since these settings only pay off on the handful of "
"very large repositories that need them."
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1651
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-scalar-option"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1653
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"options.programs.git.scalar = {\n"
"  enable = lib.mkEnableOption \"scalar\";"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1656
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  repo = lib.mkOption {\n"
"    type = lib.types.listOf lib.types.str;\n"
"    default = [ ];\n"
"    example = [ \"${config.home.homeDirectory}/NixOS/nixpkgs\" ];\n"
"  };\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1664
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-scalar"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1666
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"scalar = {\n"
"  enable = true;\n"
"  repo = [ "
"\"${config.programs.git.settings.ghq.root}/github.com/natsukium/nixpkgs\" "
"];\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1672
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-scalar-config"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1674
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(lib.mkIf scalarCfg.enable {\n"
"  programs.git = {\n"
"    settings = {\n"
"      scalar.repo = scalarCfg.repo;\n"
"      maintenance.repo = scalarCfg.repo;\n"
"    };\n"
"    includes = map (repo: {\n"
"      condition = \"gitdir:${repo}/\";\n"
"      contents = {\n"
"        core = {\n"
"          multipackindex = true;\n"
"          preloadindex = true;\n"
"          untrackedcache = true;\n"
"          autocrlf = false;\n"
"          safecrlf = false;\n"
"          fsmonitor = true;\n"
"        };\n"
"        am.keepcr = true;\n"
"        credential = {\n"
"          \"https://dev.azure.com\".usehttppath = true;\n"
"          validate = false;\n"
"        };\n"
"        gc.auto = 0;\n"
"        gui.gcwarning = false;\n"
"        index = {\n"
"          threads = true;\n"
"          version = 4;\n"
"        };\n"
"        merge = {\n"
"          stat = false;\n"
"          renames = true;\n"
"        };\n"
"        pack = {\n"
"          usebitmaps = false;\n"
"          usesparse = true;\n"
"        };\n"
"        receive.autogc = false;\n"
"        feature = {\n"
"          manyfiles = false;\n"
"          experimental = false;\n"
"        };\n"
"        fetch = {\n"
"          unpacklimit = 1;\n"
"          writecommitgraph = false;\n"
"          showforcedupdates = false;\n"
"        };\n"
"        status.aheadbehind = false;\n"
"        commitgraph.generationversion = 1;\n"
"        log.excludedecoration = \"refs/prefetch/*\";\n"
"        maintenance = {\n"
"          auto = false;\n"
"          strategy = \"incremental\";\n"
"        };\n"
"      };\n"
"    }) scalarCfg.repo;\n"
"  };\n"
"})"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:1733
#, no-wrap
msgid "GitHub CLI"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1735
msgid ""
"[[https://cli.github.com/][gh]] (GitHub CLI) is enabled alongside git "
"because it provides a credential helper "
"([[https://nix-community.github.io/home-manager/options.xhtml#opt-programs.gh.gitCredentialHelper.enable][=programs.gh.gitCredentialHelper.enable=]], "
"on by default) that transparently handles HTTPS authentication for GitHub "
"repositories. This is why the [[*URL Rewriting][=pushInsteadOf=]] setting "
"may not be exercised in practice — =gh='s auth context covers both fetch and "
"push over HTTPS."
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1741
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-gh"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1743
#, no-wrap
msgid "programs.gh.enable = true;"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:1746
#, no-wrap
msgid "Delta"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1748
msgid ""
"[[https://github.com/dandavison/delta][delta]] provides syntax-highlighted "
"diffs in the terminal with line numbers and side-by-side view "
"support. Chosen for its clean visual presentation."
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1751
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-delta"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1753
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"programs.delta = {\n"
"  enable = true;\n"
"  enableGitIntegration = true;\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:1759
#, no-wrap
msgid "Difftastic"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1761
msgid ""
"[[https://github.com/Wilfred/difftastic][Difftastic]] is a structural diff "
"tool that operates at the AST level rather than comparing lines. It "
"understands that moving a function or renaming a variable is a single "
"semantic change, not a block of deletions and insertions. This is "
"particularly valuable for JSX refactoring, indentation shifts, and nested "
"tag restructuring, where line-based diffs produce noisy, hard-to-read "
"output."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1767
msgid ""
"Both difftastic and [[*Delta][delta]] are kept because they serve "
"complementary roles: delta enhances git's built-in line diffs with syntax "
"highlighting for everyday operations (=git diff=, =git log=), while "
"difftastic is reached for via [[*Lazygit][lazygit]] when structural "
"understanding matters."
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1772
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-difftastic"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1774
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"programs.difftastic = {\n"
"  enable = true;\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:1779
#, no-wrap
msgid "Lazygit"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1781
msgid ""
"[[https://github.com/jesseduffield/lazygit][Lazygit]] is a terminal UI for "
"git. A TUI was chosen over raw git commands for interactive operations like "
"staging individual hunks, interactive rebase, and conflict resolution, where "
"the visual feedback loop significantly reduces errors. Previously used "
"gitui, but switched to lazygit for its broader feature set — gitui's "
"performance advantage did not materialize in practice, and it lacked several "
"workflow-critical operations."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1787
msgid ""
"Performance degrades noticeably on large repositories like nixpkgs, but the "
"ergonomics and active development make it a trusted part of the workflow "
"despite this tradeoff."
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1790
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-lazygit"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1792
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"programs.lazygit = {\n"
"  enable = true;\n"
"  settings = {\n"
"    <<lazygit-gui>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1797
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <<lazygit-git>>\n"
"  };\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:1802
#, no-wrap
msgid "GUI"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1804
msgid "Enable Nerd Font icons in the lazygit interface for visual clarity."
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1806
#, no-wrap
msgid "lazygit-gui"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1808
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"gui = {\n"
"  showIcons = true;\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:1813
#, no-wrap
msgid "Git Integration"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1815
msgid ""
"=overrideGpg = true= tells lazygit to run git commands inline instead of "
"spawning a subprocess for GPG/SSH signing. By default, lazygit defers to a "
"subprocess so the user can type a passphrase interactively. However, this "
"subprocess mode prevents lazygit from orchestrating interactive rebase "
"internally — rewording, reordering, or editing any commit other than HEAD is "
"[[https://github.com/jesseduffield/lazygit/issues/1146][disabled entirely]] "
"because the rebase would trigger multiple signing prompts that lazygit "
"cannot handle mid-rebase. With =overrideGpg = true=, lazygit assumes the "
"signing agent (ssh-agent, macOS Keychain) caches the passphrase, so no "
"interactive prompt is needed and all rebase operations work normally."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1824
msgid ""
"The pager configuration integrates both [[*Delta][delta]] and "
"[[*Difftastic][difftastic]] into lazygit's diff views.  Delta provides "
"syntax-highlighted line diffs (=--dark --paging=never= since lazygit handles "
"its own paging), and difftastic is available as the external diff command "
"for [[*Difftastic][structural comparison]]."
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1829
#, no-wrap
msgid "lazygit-git"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1831
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"git = {\n"
"  overrideGpg = true;\n"
"  pagers = [\n"
"    {\n"
"      colorArg = \"always\";\n"
"      pager = \"delta --dark --paging=never\";\n"
"    }\n"
"    {\n"
"      externalDiffCommand = \"difft --color=always\";\n"
"    }\n"
"  ];\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:1845
#, no-wrap
msgid "Fish Abbreviations"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1847
msgid ""
"Shell abbreviations for frequent git operations. Abbreviations (not aliases) "
"are used because fish expands them inline before execution, making the "
"actual command visible in history and allowing modification before running."
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1851
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-fish-abbreviations"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1853
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"programs.fish.shellAbbrs = {\n"
"  <<git-abbr-push>>\n"
"  <<git-abbr-pull>>\n"
"  <<git-abbr-commit>>\n"
"  <<git-abbr-status>>\n"
"  <<git-abbr-stash>>\n"
"  <<git-abbr-switch>>\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:1863
#, no-wrap
msgid "Push"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1865
msgid ""
"Force push with lease — safer than =--force= as it prevents overwriting "
"remote changes not yet fetched."
msgstr ""

